TABLE I: Errors of tracking a static needle (upper table) and a moving needle (lower table) with 5 detected feature points.
œÉùúé\sigma (in pixels) is the standard deviation of the noise added to the detected needle points in the simulation environment to imitate noisy detections in real-world scenarios.
The results show that our proposed observation model, 2 points + EM, achieves the lowest tracking error in all cases.
